n short, compose with colour in the same way as we have composed with form. This is how architecture is transformed into urbanism." Historical documents and drawings make this handy-sized volume an invaluable guide for visitors and a practical introduction for all architectural enthusiasts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitektur. 4aFrankreich. 4aLe Corbusier. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aFeugas, Jean-Pierre, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLe Roy, Bernard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVeyret, Jean-Luc, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 1990 - 1999z9783110635768oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLC Online Paketz9783035606034oZDB-23-LCO0 cprintz978376435808240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560308840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035603088423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035603088/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GAAc1990d1999  aZDB-23-LCO